.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[CR]Infinity\f[R] is a property of the \f[I]global object\f[R].
In other words, it is a variable in global scope.
.PP
The value \f[CR]Infinity\f[R] (positive infinity) is greater than any
other number.
.PP
This value behaves slightly differently than mathematical infinity; see
\f[CR]Number.POSITIVE_INFINITY\f[R] for details.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using Infinity
.IP
.EX
